        <abstract>
            <p>Discusses dimorphism in plants, especially the Rubiaceae.</p>
            <p>Gives observations on orchids; notes varying degrees of self-sterility and a varying success at crossing distinct species.</p>
            <p>Mentions local ferns he is collecting</p>
            <p>and considers the phenomenon of apparently mimetic plants.</p>
        </abstract>
